INSERT INTO service_faqs (service_page_id, question, answer, faq_order) VALUES
  (869, 'What are common electrical code violations in Pacific Palisades commercial buildings?', 'Pacific Palisades businesses often encounter outdated grounding systems, insufficient circuit protection, improper bonding, and aging panel configurations that no longer meet current National Electrical Code standards. Shaffer Construction specializes in identifying these violations and implementing corrections that bring your facility into full compliance while minimizing business disruption. Our experienced team understands the specific challenges of Pacific Palisades commercial spaces, from retail shops in the Village to office buildings and professional services offices.', 1),
  (869, 'How quickly can Shaffer Construction address code violations discovered in Pacific Palisades?', 'We respond promptly to code violations in Pacific Palisades because we understand that non-compliance creates liability and potential operational restrictions for your business. After an initial assessment, we develop a phased correction plan that can be customized to your schedule—whether you need immediate critical fixes or a comprehensive upgrade over time. Our team works efficiently to complete corrections with minimal downtime to your operations.', 2),
  (869, 'Do older commercial buildings in Pacific Palisades typically need electrical code updates?', 'Yes, many established Pacific Palisades commercial properties—including long-standing retail locations, offices, and hospitality businesses—have electrical systems that predate current code requirements. Code standards have evolved significantly over the past 20+ years to improve safety and accommodate modern electrical loads. Shaffer Construction can evaluate your building''s electrical system and recommend the updates needed to ensure compliance and safety for your tenants and customers.', 3),
  (869, 'What happens if we ignore electrical code violations in our Pacific Palisades business?', 'Non-compliant electrical systems pose serious risks: fire hazards, equipment damage, liability exposure, and potential operational restrictions from building inspectors or fire officials. Correcting violations proactively protects your business, employees, and customers while demonstrating responsible property management. Shaffer Construction provides comprehensive code compliance solutions so you can operate with confidence and peace of mind in Pacific Palisades.', 4),
  (869, 'Can Shaffer Construction handle code corrections without shutting down our Pacific Palisades business?', 'Absolutely. We work closely with Pacific Palisades commercial property owners to plan corrections strategically, often phasing work to keep your business operational. Our team coordinates with inspectors, manages permits, and uses efficient installation methods to complete code compliance work with minimal service interruption. Contact us for a free consultation to discuss a compliance plan tailored to your business needs.', 5);
